    "recap_headline": "Lehigh University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PHILADELPHIA \u2013 The Lehigh baseball team dropped a 15-2 decision to Penn in seven innings Wednesday afternoon at Meiklejohn Stadium. The Quakers notched 13 hits and capitalized off of eight walks and three Lehigh errors.\nSeniors\nOwen Walewander\nand\nRyan Davis\ndrove in runs for the Mountain Hawks, who managed five hits against Quaker pitching.\nThe loss drops Lehigh to 5-13 while Penn improves to 4-10.\nGavin Degnan went 2-for-4 with five RBIs to lead Penn.\nThe Quakers scored the game's first six runs, plating two in the first, three in the second and one in the third.\nWalewander singled home junior\nJasper Adelman\nin the fifth to put Lehigh on the board, and the following inning saw Davis double to the gap in left center, scoring\nMax Dantoni\n.\nPenn used an eight-run sixth inning to put the game out of reach.\nThree of Lehigh's five hits were doubles, with senior\nAidan Quinn\nand sophomore\nIan Wirtz\njoining Davis. Senior\nDom Patrizi\ndrew two walks, while Adelman reached twice via a walk and a hit by pitch.\nLehigh used seven pitchers Wednesday, with senior\nBrandon Coughlin\nstarting and taking the loss after giving up two first inning runs.\nThe Mountain Hawks will resume Patriot League play this weekend when they host Holy Cross for a three-game series at J. David Walker Field. A doubleheader is set for Saturday at noon followed by a single game Sunday at 1 p.m.",
